<br>
Level requirement: if you dont know anyone in guild RL its 58<br>
<br>
Equipment: Should have epic, or better, or be prepared to wait a good while (cant stand whining for help in /gu lol). Resist gear nice, but its not the end of the world.<br>
<br>
Guild events whenever something spawns and we can conjure up 3 or more clerics...<br>
<br>
Expectations of a Guildmate are outlined in the charter, if Acid has bothered to get the link working. Otherwise its fairly straightforward and can be summed up in one sentence: &quot;Think of others before you think of yourself.&quot;<br>
<br>
No minimum or maximum expectations of attendance, we tend to be an older (RL) and in some cases married set of folks, so we understand RL happens. However there are loot consequences to unexcused long absences. Refusal to raid whilst online is frowned upon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Check out the roster and keep in touch with an officer, come to some raids, be they Rumble/RoS 3 group things, or NToV insanity. The more folks get to know you the quicker the app process goes.<br>
<br>
Malagis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6D6B6B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub61.ezboard.com/ukaal60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaal60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#84A552>(8/31/02 5:08:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub61.ezboard.com/fthehand90785frm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interested in joining The Hand</span><hr size=1> I appreciate the info and time to answer my questions.  When the cable guy gets my internet fixed, I will talk with a few members and see about attending some events. <br>
